Fred Joseph WINKLER, Petitioner-Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Respondent-Appellee. No. 31095

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. July 13, 1971. Fred Joseph Winkler, pro se. Edward J. Witten, Jacksonville, Fla. (Ct. Appt.), for petitioner-appellant. Seagal V. Wheatley, U. S. Atty., Victor K. Sizemore, Asst. U. S. Atty., for respondent-appellee.

Before JOHN R. BROWN, Chief Judge, and INGRAHAM and RONEY, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir.; see Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5th Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5th Cir. 1970, 430 F.2d 966.
